sec.p:
Individual testicular cell types such as SG, SCs, spermatids, and Leydig cells were captured via LMD into 40 μL of RIPA buffer containing 0.1 mol/L phenylmethylsulfonyl fluoride (Sigma-Aldrich) and mini protease inhibitor cocktail (Roche Applied Science, Indianapolis, Indiana) in a 200 μL PCR tube cap. Laser microdissection was performed within 2 hours for each cell type. The samples were stored at −70°C and pooled together prior to processing. To maintain the uniformity of the LMD extracted proteins, equal square micrometer (μm
2
) of the pooled samples contained approximately 10 000 to 20 000 cells per cell stage. The samples were then processed by boiling with Laemmli loading buffer at 100°C for 5 minutes. The proteins in the cell lysates were subsequently separated using sodium dodecyl sulfate-polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis, and transferred onto a nitrocellulose membrane. Nonspecific antibody binding was blocked using 5% NFDM in 1× TBS for 1 hour. The blots were then incubated in 1% NFDM in TBS with 0.05% Tween 20 (TBS-T) overnight at 4°C with following antibodies; anti-MAGEA4, anti-PRM2, anti-COX6B2 1:1000, and anti-HSPA2 1:1000. The blots were washed with TBS-T and incubated with HRP-conjugated goat-anti-rabbit, goat-anti-mouse, or donkey anti-goat secondary antibodies 1:10 000 (Santa Cruz Biotechnology) for 1 hour at room temperature. The cell-specific marker proteins MAGEA4, HSPA2, COX6B2, PRM2, and the reference protein β-tubulin were detected using SuperSignal West Femto Maximum Sensitivity Chemiluminescence Substrate (Thermoscientific). The protein samples were normalized to β-tubulin.
